On Jan=
 6, 2008, at 8:43 PM, Ron wrote:




I see that there is some speculation a=
bout the eBay auctions so want to put it to bed...As I stated at the beginn=
ing of the MiniBox project, the goal is to get as many MiniBoxes into resea=
rchers&#39; hands as possible, and considered eBay as a marketing possibility. =
I arranged for two Boxes to go on the block with no reserves to see what op=
en bidding would bring.As it happens, both units went to active researchers=
 on this forum, so in that respect I&#39;m glad it worked out that way. However=
 both units went at low prices, one below cost, so in order to survive we h=
ad to set a reserve for future auctions.We have also solicited active feedb=
ack from all our users so that new ideas and improvements can be added down=
 the line. I&#39;m pleased that Bruce and Steve have been extremely helpful wit=
h their ideas and suggestions.Also, I want it understood that Frank and I h=
ave an ongoing dialog regarding designs, uses of the Box, improvements and =
so on. We have a free and open exchange of ideas. I have asked him to let m=
e know if he ever has any problems with using his name. Moreover, anyone re=
ading the literature and comments regarding Frank that I have made can see =
that they are solely to give him credit for his work, and to quote things h=
e has said or written to me.I think many good things come from persons dedi=
cated to a goal. I commend Mike C. for his efforts re: the Shack Hack, and =
consider it a great starting place for those who are technically inclined a=
nd on a budget. The search for other suitable radios should commence, if it=
 hasn&#39;t already. The key is to cooperate with each other and share informat=
ion and results. ASUP will be holding an orientation class and training ses=
sion for users of the Box at its next meeting. They will be researching usi=
ng a strict testing protocol, and recording each session as it happens. Ove=
r time, teams using the same gear should be able to collect information whi=
ch can be collated and studied for patterns. This is the next step in ITC r=
esearch, and one which can provide the hard evidence.Ron RParanormalSystems=
.com







